s l o w d o w n . . . 

in the rush of life, don’t overlook the magic in the small moments. oftentimes, we spend so much energy chasing the next ‘big’ milestone or moment, that we overlook the everyday beauty right in front of us.

laughing with loved ones, savoring a warm cup of coffee, a kind word from a stranger… these moments matter much more than we tend to give them credit for.

cherish each day. 🤍

amidst the clamor of this world, may we find solace in the gentle whispers of heaven. the noise can be overwhelming, pulling us in every direction, but deep within, there lies a longing for something more, something sacred.

in the stillness of the soul, we can discern the echoes of eternity, softly reminding us to set our gaze on what truly matters. lean in.🫶🏽
an eternal perspective shifts everything. 🤍
Jesus, you are worth it all.

stop and take the picture.
say ‘i love you’ even when you feel you’ve said it enough.
give a stranger a compliment.
try the new recipe.
apologize. mean it.
call the loved one.
pause, and bask in gratitude.
talk to Jesus. make space to hear Him talk back.
and remember, that the ‘little’ moments never really are that little. cherish them. 🤍

every moment,
every challenge,
every tear,
every triumph,
He is weaving together for your good.
you may not see it now, but one day, you’ll realize that He’s had your back all along.

there are many experiences in this life that mold, refine, and shape us into the likeness of Jesus, reminding us of the depths of his love along the way. but nothing has opened my eyes to God’s love for me like my love for my son.

there are many moments in the journey of motherhood that i doubt myself… am i doing the right thing? did i show up the best i could today? on and on… maybe you can relate. however, the love that flows from within me into him is the one thing that i could never doubt for a second. i would give it all up in a moment’s notice for him. and to imagine, that is just a GLIMPSE of how our Father feels about us. really think about that.

thank you Jesus for the chance to experience your love for us as we love the children you have entrusted us with. there will never be anything else like it.

I hope when I look back one day on the journey that is this life, I look back knowing I was present. That I took the extra time, showed up when it mattered the most, and didn’t take for granted the moments that often seem fleeting in the moment. That I didn’t become so attached to my to do lists and plans that I forgot how to just BE, and that my heart and home are filled with memories of days just like this.

reminder: motherhood is what you make it.

here’s to doing away with the stereotype that life is over after kids, and embracing every season (the still, the busy, the adventurous, and every one in between) that life brings, with them by your side. 🤍

I say this because I’ve been there. I’ve been in the place where I’ve asked myself “how could you let God down like this after everything He’s done for you”? “Do you even love Him”? I’ve been in the place of being consumed by shame and condemnation, allowing it to silence the voice of God within me. I’ve been in the place of questioning it all. My relationship with God, my salvation, all of it.

But man, am I thankful for a God that convicts instead of condemns. That loves instead of leaves, even when I don’t deserve it. That saw every stumbling block, every detour, every obstacle, and still went before the cross so that I might one day know the true meaning of unconditional love.

Setbacks aren’t stopping points.

lay it down. 🤍

 “Come to me, all you who are weary and burdened, and I will give you rest. Take my yoke upon you and learn from me, for I am gentle and humble in heart, and you will find rest for your souls. For my yoke is easy and my burden is light.” Matthew 11:28-30

You can trust Him 🤍

Romans 8:28 — and we know that for those who love God, ALL things work together for good, for those who are called according to His purpose.

You don’t have to have it all figured out. You don’t have to have the perfect prayer, or the “right” words, or the polished appearance to come before God. Come as you are — whether that be burdened, weary, anxious, or doubtful. Come as you are, and lay it all before Him. He sees. He cares. And He’s waiting on you to come home. 🤍
where God calls, God equips. take the step. 🤍
When you reach the end of your strength, remember, God is only at the beginning of His. Rest. He’s got this, and He’s got you. 🤍

they’ll tell you it’s a burden. that you lose your sense of self, that your identity will get lost in the role you now assume. they’ll tell you “just wait…”, projecting their own discontentment onto you before you’ve even gotten to have certain experiences for yourself.

but sister, i am here to remind you of the beauty in the sacred calling that is motherhood. a calling that, while carrying its challenges, will continually mold you into the likeness of our King as you embody what it means to unconditionally love in an entirely new way. a calling that reshapes your identity, refines your spirit, and transforms your mind. a calling that will fill you with a ferocity you wouldn’t imagine, an authority uniquely yours, and a gentleness that only a mother can carry.

what a gift it is to raise this generation of God’s children. what an honor to steward their little hearts, BIG emotions (🤪), and equip them for the world ahead. just wait… because your best days are ahead of you.

when i truly realized i wasn’t meant to shoulder the weight of this life on my own, everything changed. i used to think holding it all together made me strong… now i understand that there’s immense strength in our surrender. i don’t know what it is for you, but God does. bring it to the feet of Jesus. 🤍

cultivating a home isn’t about the “things” that fill it. it’s about how people feel when they’re in your midst. it’s about cultivating a space where people are safe to show up fully as they are, and it’s about cultivating a space where the roots of love run deep. 🫶🏽

last night, my dad had an unexpected overnight layover in my city. he didn’t get in until midnight and was flying out early the next morning, so i scooped him up, and we headed to Waffle House for a 1AM “breakfast”. as we sat catching up, i thought about how incredibly rare it is for us these days to actually get one on one time together (let alone see one another more than maybe 2-3x a year) and how i wished we could have more of these moments.

this morning, i heard this clip, and it really hit me. now i know these numbers are not 100% accurate — for some, it could be much more; for others, much less. but nonetheless, it was a reminder to take every opportunity that’s given to spend time. make the late night drive. clear your schedule to travel and see them. the older we get, the fewer we have the chance.

cherish the moments you have, while you have them. 🤍

I once heard it said, “if I get to the end of my life having lived for Jesus and find out I had it all wrong, I’ve lost nothing, but if I get to the end of my life having denied him and then find out I had it all wrong, I’ve lost everything”, and truer words have never been spoken.

When we reach the end of our days, it will not matter what success we attained on earth, how “good” we were according to our subjective moral standards, how we tried to manifest our destiny, or how many material things we possessed.

What will matter is the relationship we had with Jesus. What will matter is how we kept an eternal perspective in fallen world. How we lived in spirit and in truth.  How we loved the ones around us. Believers, let’s keep our eyes up, our heart posture aligned, and always remember that the greatest gift we could ever receive is the one we received on a cross 2,000 years ago.

If I’m being honest…

This has been one of the hardest years of my life. It has been a year of intense refining, faith-stretching, prolonged waiting, and heart examining. A year where I learned to cherish the small pockets of joy because at times it felt like they were all I had. A year where I learned (and am still learning) not only what it means to delight myself in the Lord, but to be reminded, again and again, that despite how I often felt, that He truly delights in me too.

There’s only so much we see of one another’s lives in these spaces. So much room for assumption, comparison, and then some. So much surface-level connection, and so. much. noise. But this is a reminder that we’re all going through and growing through so much more than meets the eye. If you’re reading this right now, I want you to know, God sees. He sees the battles fought behind closed doors. The tears poured out in the secret place. This year may have been hard, but blessed are the challenges that draw us that much closer to the heart of the Father.

Through it all, I am grateful, I am expectant, and I am so, so excited, for what God has in store for the season ahead. The best is yet to come. For me, and for you. 🫶🏽

BEGINNER SOURDOUGH RECIPE 👇🏽 (im super visual so i thought a little video going through the process would be helpful 🫶🏽)
- Add 150 g active sourdough starter & 350 g warm water to glass bowl // whisk 
- Add in 500g bread flour & 8g sea salt // mix w/ hands and scrape any excess flour off bowl (sometimes I transfer dough out, clean bowl and then put it back in)
- Cover with cotton towel and leave on counter for an hour
- Do first set of stretch and folds // cover & leave on counter for 1h 
- Stretch and folds again, cover leave for 1h
- Stretch and fold 3rd time then cover and leave to bulk ferment (until doubled in size // 2-3 h usually)
- Once fermentation is done and doubled in size, dump dough out on floured surface and preshape
- Let dough rest for 10-20 minutes on counter and then do final shaping
- Sprinkle flour in proofing basket and place dough bottom side up into proofing basket
- Option 1 // proof on counter for ~2-3h (can vary based on temp levels in home) then bake
- Option 2 // proof overnight in fridge (just place proofing basket in fridge covered with  cotton towel) and bake in am
When ready to bake 
- score bread (one big score + any fun designs if you want to add)
- preheat oven with Dutch oven inside on 450 for 30 min
- Put bread inside of Dutch oven with parchment paper
- Bake 20 min with lid on on 450
- Remove lid and bake another 40 min lid off on 400
- Take out and let cool for 1.5h BEFORE cutting 

ENJOY 🤍 & stay tuned because I am in my bread era there may be more where this came from coming soon 😉

to the hopeful mother waiting on the Lord… 👇🏽

I know its hard right now. Hard to look around and see others with the very thing your heart is longing for. Hard to keep the faith when it feels like you’ve been in a season of waiting for so long. Hard to ignore the societal timelines and pressures coming at you from every angle.

But be encouraged, that despite how cliche it may sound, God’s promises for you are ALWAYS worth waiting for. You may not see it now, but one day you will… and your life (and your children’s lives) will be a testament to the glory of God.

As you are reading this, I pray right now over your heart and over your womb. May the God who knit you together in your own mother’s womb protect yours as you await the child for which you have prayed, and keep you in perfect peace as you wait on His promise. May you remember that you can come to Him in all of your raw emotions, and lay your burdens at His feet. And may you know, that He is working all things together for your good, even when we don’t understand the why or how.

Your time is coming. Don’t lose faith.

my approach to “refreshing my home” 👇🏽

〰️ one space at a time, one day at a time
this year, we’re not overwhelming ourselves with huge draining tasks that leave us empty and unable to be fully present with the ones we love. instead, we’re refreshing things one space at a time, one day at a time. (and let’s be real, i have a toddler so this decision was kind of made for me lol)

〰️subtract before you add
before adding to your spaces, go through them, declutter, minimize where you can, and make sure that anything you decide to add comes from a place of intentionality and not just standard consumerism.

〰️be resourceful
before i started organizing my kitchen today, i was CERTAIN i needed a trip to the container store, potentially extra storage space, etc., and after decluttering and reorganizing the storage spaces i had to work with, i ended up with a space for everything without needing anything extra!

deep cleaning can be overwhelming sometimes, but it can also be the perfect reset for the soul heading into a new year. 10/10 recommend (when done at your own pace in your own way). 🫶🏽

to have children that are covered, protected in the spirit, surrounded by the Word of God… this is both the greatest gift, and our greatest responsibility.

let us not take it lightly. 🫶🏽

MY 2024 INS & OUTS — 

this year, we’re keeping boundaries with social media (started this at the end of last year and it’s actually changed my life), having our daily sleepy girl magnesium mocktail, reading our (physical!!!) bibles, and staying disciplined.

we are NOT: comparing, impulse spending, being lukewarm, or holding onto grudges (and also can we just be done with QR code menus??? pls)
